Darin,

Try running python example &#39;mix1.py&#39;.  This uses a Valve object, and 
works for me.  One thing that would likely cause a segmentation 
violation is if the Valve &#39;massFlowRate&#39; method is called without the 
Valve installed between an upsteam and a downstream reactor.  This 
method calls the &#39;pressure&#39; method of both connected reactors, and will 
  fail if one or both are not connected.

Dave


